metadata.name: We Are Alone Together #447
metadata.description:
We meander through the flows of life, alone but together. This experience — an ultimately solitary one — is communicated but never truly shared. Our consciousnesses live in a perpetual separated state, alone but together.

############

Display resolution scales with window size. Press ’h’ (in live mode) to generate a 6000x7500 hi-res image. This may take a few seconds to generate depending on your hardware. Press ‘d’ to redraw the artwork.

Original artwork by perkwerk * made with p5.js * 2022

metadata.name: Sleepless #45
metadata.description:
Sleepless is a generative art project made from p5.js. Inspired by the artist's travels, the project emulates a window view of a distant city at night. Variations include randomization of different window elements (frames and bars) and city elements (buildings, planes and ships). It is also mintable in several foreground and background colors. The colors and dithering were selected to create a charcoal texture.

Press 'S' to download a high res PNG.
Due to the preview image being compressed to fit your window size, the dithering may look different from the high res PNG.

NFTs minted are under the NFT License 2.0 (https://www.nftlicense.org/)

metadata.name: Balanced #105
A Bugged Forest #339
metadata.description:
A forest has stories to tell.
About times that were, about times that will be.
-
This project was minted in much unusual conditions. 
We gathered here, by 38 degrees heat. We belong to a crowd who loves stories, of civilisations at stake and deities, of afterlife and worship. We drank and hugged and chanted pagan hymns. We minted the Bugged Forest from our place on earth that we call Hell just for the fun of it. We are passionate, and loving, and angry and desperate. We, people of the soil, under a bugged sun.
-
This project is the long-form version of an algorithm that contains a bug. “The Bugged Tree”’s code was salvaged and stored and served as the core motivation and engine for an entire forest. Its concept is about releasing the control. I am a  byproduct of evolution, an iteration of that specie who wanted utter control, and which at some point, lost control over its own creation. As a generative artist, I chose to welcome the event of chance into my creative process. The symbolism in chance made me feel humble and free. Unwilling to make any change to a story that the Tree needed to tell me, as a listener, rather than a writer of my own idealised fantasies.
-
The iterations aren’t under control. They may be odd and off. We have to accept it. They are also plottable, press [s] in live mode to get a SVG. Attempt the plot at your own risk, as there’s a possibility for it to come near to impossibilities or cause paper or motor damage, and most certainly, a bugged drawing.
-
From Earth or from Hell, with love, yours truthfully, NFTBiker and zancan

metadata.name: Updraft #213
metadata.description:
UPDRAFT seeks to reproduce the beauty of tornadoes and other vortices in a minimalist style and simple shapes, thus highlighting the purity of the lines of these fascinating objects.

If the tornado of life scares you, remember that while you will probably be a little shaken and confused on your journey, you will end up at the top of it. That's the beauty of the updraft.

[S] or [Double-Tap] when viewing in full screen to save a 4000x4000 PNG image

Artist: Estienne
August 2022
Made with p5.js
Best viewed on Chrome or Chromium-based browsers

metadata.name: Afterglow Kaleido #245
metadata.description:
Afterglow Kaleido explores the variaty of organically animated shapes combined with the kaleidoscope (multi-mirroring) technique and an afterglow effect.
Generative token varies in mirror-count, animation-direction, -speed, size and complexity.

In Live-View or when iframe is focused...
...click/tap or hit space to pause animation
...hit 'r' or tap with 3 fingers to reset animation to initial, paused state.


Created with p5.js using post5.

- @TeNinEightNFTs

objkt.name: To my lips, your kisses and cigarettes #57

metadata.name: To my lips, your kisses and cigarettes #57
metadata.description:
A timid smoke rises from the ashtray, just a trace of what had been hours before, powerful smoke drifting through the room. A memory of the lighted flames illuminating the faces that were there, coming from many mouths, amid laughter, sips, drags, and lipsticks. 
Red, purple, orange, pink, beige... an ashtray of many palettes, an ashtray of many mouths. 
The smoke goes out and, like the fog that dissipates in the early hours of the day clearing the horizon, I realize: Sophie, Chloe, Lena, Zoe and Kylie... which of these mouths also took my heart?

15 layers
47 images
More than a trillion possibilities 

Laura Faria | @laufaria
2022
Digital Collage
